<p>This way of thinking, the validation of the value of decentralized social networks, was also <a href="https://mastodon.social/@atomicpoet/110000249690410261" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank" referrerpolicy="no-referrer">echoed here</a> by Chris Trottier, who <a href="https://mastodon.social/@atomicpoet/110001544112104104" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank" referrerpolicy="no-referrer">further added</a> that all Meta’s recent successes are either acquired or copied, giving him confidence that it will not be easy for Meta to take over the fediverse. He also <a href="https://mastodon.social/@atomicpoet/110000357375424899" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank" referrerpolicy="no-referrer">emphases </a>the validation that this gives to the decentralized social networks, enabling and confirming other developers that want to work on the fediverse. </p>



